@page
@model ProjectManagement.Areas.Admin.Pages.Help.IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Administration guide";
}

<partial name="~/Areas/Admin/Pages/Shared/_AdminPageHeader.cshtml" model="Model.Header" />

<div class="admin-guide-layout">
    <div class="admin-guide-sections">
        <section id="people-access" class="admin-panel admin-guide-section">
            <header class="admin-panel__header">
                <div><div class="admin-panel__eyebrow">People and access</div><h2>User lifecycle</h2></div>
                <i class="bi bi-people" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </header>
            <div class="admin-guide-section__body">
                <p>Use <strong>Disable</strong> when sign-in must stop while records, ownership and attribution remain intact. Password reset issues a temporary credential, invalidates current sessions and requires a change at the next sign-in.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Review the complete account page before changing privileged roles.</li>
                    <li>Do not disable or remove the final active Administrator account.</li>
                    <li>Use deletion only when the lifecycle and retention safeguards permit it.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="access-governance" class="admin-panel admin-guide-section">
            <header class="admin-panel__header">
                <div><div class="admin-panel__eyebrow">Access governance</div><h2>Roles, capabilities and privileged accounts</h2></div>
                <i class="bi bi-shield-check" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </header>
            <div class="admin-guide-section__body">
                <p>The Access Governance page explains which configured role grants each administrative capability and identifies privileged account conditions requiring review.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Role and policy composition remains code-defined; the governance page is a review surface, not a dynamic policy editor.</li>
                    <li>Disabled or deletion-pending accounts may retain role assignments for historical and restoration purposes.</li>
                    <li>Maintain more than one active Administrator where organisational policy permits.</li>
                    <li>Export the bounded access-review file for formal review or record keeping.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="monitoring" class="admin-panel admin-guide-section">
            <header class="admin-panel__header">
                <div><div class="admin-panel__eyebrow">Monitoring</div><h2>Login activity and audit logs</h2></div>
                <i class="bi bi-graph-up-arrow" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </header>
            <div class="admin-guide-section__body">
                <p>Login Activity is a security view; ERP Usage is an adoption view. A user may remain signed in for several days, so login count must not be used as a proxy for daily ERP use.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>ERP Usage records bounded navigation and interactive activity intervals without capturing keystrokes, page content or query text.</li>
                    <li>Approximate active time is an adoption indicator, not attendance or individual performance.</li>
                    <li>Failed and lockout incidents remain in Login Activity and require security review.</li>
                    <li>System Health reports readiness; a Starting or Unknown check is not equivalent to Healthy.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="recovery" class="admin-panel admin-guide-section">
            <header class="admin-panel__header">
                <div><div class="admin-panel__eyebrow">Recovery and retention</div><h2>Archive, trash and purge</h2></div>
                <i class="bi bi-arrow-counterclockwise" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </header>
            <div class="admin-guide-section__body">
                <p><strong>Archive</strong> removes a record from active operational views without invoking deletion retention. <strong>Trash</strong> starts the configured recovery period. <strong>Purge</strong> is irreversible and may remove related stored assets.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Review dependent records and storage impact before permanent deletion.</li>
                    <li>Use the exact-name and acknowledgement controls for destructive operations.</li>
                    <li>Manual and background purge operations use the same governed command path.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="maintenance" class="admin-panel admin-guide-section">
            <header class="admin-panel__header">
                <div><div class="admin-panel__eyebrow">Controlled maintenance</div><h2>Ingestion and legacy import</h2></div>
                <i class="bi bi-tools" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </header>
            <div class="admin-guide-section__body">
                <p>Run ingestion only after reviewing its preflight state. Legacy import must be validated and previewed before commit; the preview token, source digest and reconciliation report protect against accidental repeat imports.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="master-data" class="admin-panel admin-guide-section">
            <header class="admin-panel__header">
                <div><div class="admin-panel__eyebrow">Configuration governance</div><h2>Master data</h2></div>
                <i class="bi bi-sliders2" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </header>
            <div class="admin-guide-section__body">
                <p>Master data controls values used throughout PRISM. A change may affect current forms, historical reporting and future records.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Deactivate referenced values instead of deleting them.</li>
                    <li>Category deletion is permitted only when no projects, children or descendants depend on the entry.</li>
                    <li>Reordering changes presentation order; it does not rewrite historical project data.</li>
                    <li>Celebrations are calendar records and are not automatically sourced from user-account profiles.</li>
                    <li>Every create, update, status, reorder and delete operation is written to the audit trail.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>

                <section id="office-calendar" class="admin-panel admin-guide-section">
            <header class="admin-panel__header"><div><div class="admin-panel__eyebrow">Office calendar</div><h2>Gazetted and Restricted Holidays</h2></div><i class="bi bi-calendar-week" aria-hidden="true"></i></header>
            <div class="admin-guide-section__body"><p>Classification and office observance are separate decisions. Every Restricted Holiday appears on the shared calendar, but only Gazetted Holidays and RHs declared as office holidays close the office and affect future working-day calculations.</p><ul><li>Use <strong>Declare as office holiday</strong> to observe an RH office-wide.</li><li>Use <strong>Withdraw office observance</strong> to return the date to normal working status while retaining the RH for information.</li><li>Existing approved project dates are never silently recalculated.</li></ul></div>
        </section>

        <section id="configuration-integrity" class="admin-panel admin-guide-section">
            <header class="admin-panel__header">
                <div><div class="admin-panel__eyebrow">Configuration assurance</div><h2>Integrity review and controlled repair</h2></div>
                <i class="bi bi-clipboard2-check" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            </header>
            <div class="admin-guide-section__body">
                <p>Configuration Integrity checks hierarchy, naming, reference and display-order conditions without changing data.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Automatic repair is deliberately limited to deterministic display-order normalisation.</li>
                    <li>Hierarchy, duplicate-name and reference findings require record-level review.</li>
                    <li>Every repair records the affected domain, changed-record count and actor in the audit trail.</li>
                    <li>Run the integrity review after legacy import or significant taxonomy restructuring.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>
    </div>

    <aside class="admin-panel admin-guide-nav" aria-label="Guide sections">
        <header class="admin-panel__header"><div><div class="admin-panel__eyebrow">On this page</div><h2>Guide sections</h2></div></header>
        <a href="#people-access">People and access</a>
        <a href="#access-governance">Access governance</a>
        <a href="#monitoring">Monitoring</a>
        <a href="#recovery">Recovery and retention</a>
        <a href="#maintenance">Controlled maintenance</a>
        <a href="#master-data">Master data</a>
        <a href="#office-calendar">Office calendar</a>
        <a href="#configuration-integrity">Configuration integrity</a>
    </aside>
</div>

@section Scripts {
    <script src="~/js/admin/admin-help.js" asp-append-version="true" defer></script>
}
